Your pod is Pending because Multus cannot parse the network annotation JSON.
The error is very clear in the events:

parsePodNetworkAnnotation: failed to parse pod Network Attachment Selection Annotation JSON format:
invalid character '}' looking for beginning of object key string

This means the Network Attachment Definition (NAD) annotation is invalid JSON.


---

🔎 Problem Location

From your pod description:

Annotations:
k8s.v1.cni.cncf.io/networks:
[ { "name": "bscf-bh0c-nad", }, 
  { "name": "bscf-bh0c-nad", "interface": "bh1" }, 
  { "name": "bscf-bh0c-1-nad", }, 
  { "name": "bscf-bh0c-1-na...

The issue is here:

{ "name": "bscf-bh0c-nad", },

❌ Trailing comma after the field.

JSON does NOT allow trailing commas.


---

⚠️ Incorrect JSON

[
 { "name": "bscf-bh0c-nad", },
 { "name": "bscf-bh0c-nad", "interface": "bh1" },
 { "name": "bscf-bh0c-1-nad", }
]


---

✅ Correct JSON

Remove trailing commas.

[
 { "name": "bscf-bh0c-nad" },
 { "name": "bscf-bh0c-nad", "interface": "bh1" },
 { "name": "bscf-bh0c-1-nad" }
]


---

🔧 How to Fix

Edit the Deployment / Statefulset / Helm template that created this pod.

Check:

oc get deploy -n cnf | grep bscf

Then edit:

oc edit deploy bscf4000-bip0 -n cnf

Fix annotation section:

metadata:
  annotations:
    k8s.v1.cni.cncf.io/networks: |
      [
        { "name": "bscf-bh0c-nad" },
        { "name": "bscf-bh0c-nad", "interface": "bh1" },
        { "name": "bscf-bh0c-1-nad" }
      ]


---

🔄 Then restart the pod

oc delete pod bscf4000-bip0-7b86b86565-7tv2d -n cnf

ReplicaSet will recreate it.


